currentDoc:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

currentSuggestions.original: I think the main concern with this issue is that if enough people do this, then ignorance will spread through the population and more ignorant thoughts could be shared
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I think the main concern with this issue is that if enough people do this, then ignorance will spread through the population and more ignorant thoughts could be shared

currentSuggestions.original: I think all people do have some responsibility to know what's going on in the world.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I think all people do have some responsibility to know what's going on in the world.

currentSuggestions.original: Also, the news is not always truthful or informative and can sometimes cause more problems than it is trying to solve.
